From: Benoit Parrot <bparrot@ti.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jan 2014 15:20:47 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 157/285] ARM: AM437x: dts: add vpfe[0,1] module DT entries

Add Video Processing Front End (VPFE) device tree nodes for AM34xx family of devices.

Signed-off-by: Benoit Parrot <bparrot@ti.com>
Signed-off-by: Darren Etheridge <detheridge@ti.com>
[Kevin: The original patch taken from TI
ti-sdk-am437x-evm-07.01.00.00-Linux-x86-Install.bin]
Signed-off-by: Kevin Hao <kexin.hao@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/am4372.dtsi |   20 ++++++++++++++++++++
 1 files changed, 20 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/boot/dts/am4372.dtsi b/arch/arm/boot/dts/am4372.dtsi
index 036c9a6..dfa78e9 100644
--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/am4372.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/am4372.dtsi
@@ -1092,6 +1092,26 @@
 			};
 		};
 
+		vpfe0: vpfe@48326000 {
+			compatible = "ti,am437x-vpfe";
+			reg = <0x48326000 0x2000>;
+			interrupts = <GIC_SPI 48 IRQ_TYPE_LEVEL_HIGH>;
+			ti,hwmods = "vpfe0";
+			clocks = <&vpfe0_fck>;
+			clock-names = "fck";
+			status = "disabled";
+		};
+
+		vpfe1: vpfe@48328000 {
+			compatible = "ti,am437x-vpfe";
+			reg = <0x48328000 0x2000>;
+			interrupts = <GIC_SPI 50 IRQ_TYPE_LEVEL_HIGH>;
+			ti,hwmods = "vpfe1";
+			clocks = <&vpfe1_fck>;
+			clock-names = "fck";
+			status = "disabled";
+		};
+
 	};
 
 	clocks {
